WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:14.720
The Assembly will hear an address by his Excellency Donald Trump,

2
00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:14.721


3
00:00:14.721 --> 00:00:18.360
President of the United States of America.

4
00:00:18.360 --> 00:00:18.361


5
00:00:18.361 --> 00:00:32.560
I request protocol to escort his president his excellency.

6
00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:32.561


7
00:00:32.561 --> 00:00:43.360
On behalf of the General Assembly I have the honor to welcome to the United Nations His Excellency Donald Trump,

8
00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:43.361


9
00:00:43.361 --> 00:01:02.560
president of the United States of America and to invite him to address the assembly.

10
00:01:02.560 --> 00:01:02.561


11
00:01:02.561 --> 00:01:05.240
Mr. Secretary General,

12
00:01:05.240 --> 00:01:05.241


13
00:01:05.241 --> 00:01:05.760
Mr. President,

14
00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:05.761


15
00:01:05.761 --> 00:01:08.840
world leaders,

16
00:01:08.840 --> 00:01:08.841


17
00:01:08.841 --> 00:01:11.520
and distinguished delegates:

18
00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:11.521


19
00:01:11.521 --> 00:01:15.160
Welcome to New York.

20
00:01:15.160 --> 00:01:15.161


21
00:01:15.161 --> 00:01:19.120
It is a profound honor to stand here in my home city,

22
00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:19.160


23
00:01:19.160 --> 00:01:22.320
as a representative of the American people,

24
00:01:22.320 --> 00:01:22.321


25
00:01:22.321 --> 00:01:26.160
to address the people of the world.

26
00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:26.161


27
00:01:26.161 --> 00:01:34.880
As millions of our citizens continue to suffer the effects of the devastating hurricanes that have struck our country,

28
00:01:34.880 --> 00:01:34.881


29
00:01:34.881 --> 00:01:44.480
I want to begin by expressing my appreciation to every leader in this room who has offered assistance and aid.

30
00:01:44.480 --> 00:01:44.481


31
00:01:44.481 --> 00:01:47.600
The American people are strong and resilient,

32
00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:47.601


33
00:01:47.601 --> 00:01:51.760
and they will emerge from these hardships more determined than ever before.

34
00:01:51.760 --> 00:01:51.761


35
00:01:51.761 --> 00:01:53.880
Fortunately,

36
00:01:53.880 --> 00:01:53.881


37
00:01:53.881 --> 00:02:01.560
the United States has done very well since Election Day last November 8th.

38
00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:01.561


39
00:02:01.561 --> 00:02:04.560
The stock market is at an all-time high --

40
00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:05.521


41
00:02:05.521 --> 00:02:07.080
a record.

42
00:02:07.080 --> 00:02:07.081


43
00:02:07.081 --> 00:02:11.680
Unemployment is at its lowest level in 16 years,

44
00:02:11.680 --> 00:02:11.681


45
00:02:11.681 --> 00:02:15.320
and because of our regulatory and other reforms,

46
00:02:15.320 --> 00:02:15.321


47
00:02:15.321 --> 00:02:21.560
we have more people working in the United States today than ever before.

48
00:02:21.560 --> 00:02:21.561


49
00:02:21.561 --> 00:02:24.160
Companies are moving back,

50
00:02:24.160 --> 00:02:24.161


51
00:02:24.161 --> 00:02:30.800
creating job growth the likes of which our country has not seen in a very long time.

52
00:02:30.800 --> 00:02:30.801


53
00:02:30.801 --> 00:02:40.480
And it has just been announced that we will be spending almost $700 billion on our military and defense.

54
00:02:40.480 --> 00:02:40.481


55
00:02:40.481 --> 00:02:45.720
Our military will soon be the strongest it has ever been.

56
00:02:45.720 --> 00:02:45.721


57
00:02:45.721 --> 00:02:49.720
For more than 70 years,

58
00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:49.721


59
00:02:49.721 --> 00:02:51.360
in times of war and peace,

60
00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:51.361


61
00:02:51.361 --> 00:02:54.360
the leaders of nations,

62
00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:54.361


63
00:02:54.361 --> 00:02:54.960
movements,

64
00:02:54.960 --> 00:02:54.961


65
00:02:54.961 --> 00:02:58.200
and religions have stood before this assembly.

66
00:02:58.200 --> 00:02:58.201


67
00:02:58.201 --> 00:02:58.800
Like them,

68
00:02:58.800 --> 00:02:58.801


69
00:02:58.801 --> 00:03:09.800
I intend to address some of the very serious threats before us today but also the enormous potential waiting to be unleashed.

70
00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:09.801


71
00:03:09.801 --> 00:03:14.840
We live in a time of extraordinary opportunity.

72
00:03:14.840 --> 00:03:14.841


73
00:03:14.841 --> 00:03:16.200
Breakthroughs in science,

74
00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:16.201


75
00:03:16.201 --> 00:03:17.520
technology,

76
00:03:17.520 --> 00:03:17.521


77
00:03:17.521 --> 00:03:26.440
and medicine are curing illnesses and solving problems that prior generations thought impossible to solve.

78
00:03:26.440 --> 00:03:26.441


79
00:03:26.441 --> 00:03:34.480
But each day also brings news of growing dangers that threaten everything we cherish and value.

80
00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:34.481


81
00:03:34.481 --> 00:03:42.400
Terrorists and extremists have gathered strength and spread to every region of the planet.

82
00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:42.401


83
00:03:42.401 --> 00:03:56.360
Rogue regimes represented in this body not only support terrorists but threaten other nations and their own people with the most destructive weapons known to humanity.

84
00:03:56.360 --> 00:03:56.361


85
00:03:56.361 --> 00:04:04.080
Authority and authoritarian powers seek to collapse the values,

86
00:04:04.080 --> 00:04:04.081


87
00:04:04.081 --> 00:04:05.680
the systems,

88
00:04:05.680 --> 00:04:05.681


89
00:04:05.681 --> 00:04:13.840
and alliances that prevented conflict and tilted the world toward freedom since World War II.

90
00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:13.841


91
00:04:13.841 --> 00:04:19.240
International criminal networks traffic drugs,

92
00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:19.241


93
00:04:19.241 --> 00:04:19.840
weapons,

94
00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:19.841


95
00:04:19.841 --> 00:04:21.120
people;

96
00:04:21.120 --> 00:04:21.121


97
00:04:21.121 --> 00:04:24.400
force dislocation and mass migration;

98
00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:24.401


99
00:04:24.401 --> 00:04:26.120
threaten our borders;

100
00:04:26.120 --> 00:04:26.121


101
00:04:26.121 --> 00:04:32.040
and new forms of aggression exploit technology to menace our citizens.

102
00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:32.041


103
00:04:32.041 --> 00:04:34.120
To put it simply,

104
00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:34.121


105
00:04:34.121 --> 00:04:40.160
we meet at a time of both of immense promise and great peril.

106
00:04:41.360 --> 00:04:41.441


107
00:04:41.441 --> 00:04:45.680
It is entirely up to us whether we lift the world to new heights,

108
00:04:45.680 --> 00:04:45.681


109
00:04:45.681 --> 00:04:52.200
or let it fall into a valley of disrepair.

110
00:04:52.200 --> 00:04:52.201


111
00:04:52.201 --> 00:04:54.360
We have it in our power,

112
00:04:54.360 --> 00:04:54.361


113
00:04:54.361 --> 00:04:56.280
should we so choose,

114
00:04:56.280 --> 00:04:56.281


115
00:04:56.281 --> 00:04:58.000
to lift millions from poverty,

116
00:04:58.800 --> 00:04:58.881


117
00:04:58.881 --> 00:05:01.920
to help our citizens realize their dreams,

118
00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:01.921


119
00:05:01.921 --> 00:05:06.800
and to ensure that new generations of children are raised free from violence,

120
00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:06.801


121
00:05:06.801 --> 00:05:08.680
hatred,

122
00:05:08.680 --> 00:05:08.681


123
00:05:08.681 --> 00:05:10.880
and fear.

124
00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:10.881


125
00:05:10.881 --> 00:05:21.240
This institution was founded in the aftermath of two world wars to help shape this better future.

126
00:05:21.240 --> 00:05:21.241


127
00:05:21.241 --> 00:05:28.040
It was based on the vision that diverse nations could cooperate to protect their sovereignty,

128
00:05:28.040 --> 00:05:28.041


129
00:05:28.041 --> 00:05:29.880
preserve their security,

130
00:05:29.880 --> 00:05:29.881


131
00:05:29.881 --> 00:05:33.120
and promote their prosperity.

132
00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:33.121


133
00:05:33.121 --> 00:05:34.640
It was in the same period,

134
00:05:34.640 --> 00:05:34.641


135
00:05:34.641 --> 00:05:37.360
exactly 70 years ago,

136
00:05:37.360 --> 00:05:37.361


137
00:05:37.361 --> 00:05:43.000
that the United States developed the Marshall Plan to help restore Europe.

138
00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:43.001


139
00:05:43.001 --> 00:05:45.280
Those three beautiful pillars --

140
00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:45.281


141
00:05:45.281 --> 00:05:49.080
they’re pillars of peace,

142
00:05:49.080 --> 00:05:49.081


143
00:05:49.081 --> 00:05:50.640
sovereignty,

144
00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:50.641


145
00:05:50.641 --> 00:05:51.920
security,

146
00:05:51.920 --> 00:05:51.921


147
00:05:51.921 --> 00:05:52.720
and prosperity.

148
00:05:52.720 --> 00:05:52.721


149
00:05:52.721 --> 00:06:01.640
The Marshall Plan was built on the noble idea that the whole world is safer when nations are strong,

150
00:06:01.640 --> 00:06:01.641


151
00:06:01.641 --> 00:06:03.080
independent,

152
00:06:03.080 --> 00:06:03.081


153
00:06:03.081 --> 00:06:05.000
and free.

154
00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:05.001


155
00:06:05.001 --> 00:06:10.040
As President Truman said in his message to Congress at that time,

156
00:06:10.040 --> 00:06:10.041


157
00:06:10.041 --> 00:06:17.880
“Our support of European recovery is in full accord with our support of the United Nations.

158
00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:18.521


159
00:06:18.521 --> 00:06:24.440
The success of the United Nations depends upon the independent strength of its members.”

160
00:06:24.440 --> 00:06:24.441


161
00:06:24.441 --> 00:06:31.040
To overcome the perils of the present and to achieve the promise of the future,

162
00:06:31.840 --> 00:06:31.921


163
00:06:31.921 --> 00:06:35.760
we must begin with the wisdom of the past.

164
00:06:35.760 --> 00:06:35.761


165
00:06:35.761 --> 00:06:45.240
Our success depends on a coalition of strong and independent nations that embrace their sovereignty to promote security,

166
00:06:45.240 --> 00:06:45.241


167
00:06:45.241 --> 00:06:46.040
prosperity,

168
00:06:46.040 --> 00:06:46.041


169
00:06:46.041 --> 00:06:50.400
and peace for themselves and for the world.

170
00:06:52.320 --> 00:06:52.401


171
00:06:52.401 --> 00:06:58.200
We do not expect diverse countries to share the same cultures,

172
00:06:58.200 --> 00:06:58.201


173
00:06:58.201 --> 00:06:59.160
traditions,

174
00:06:59.160 --> 00:06:59.161


175
00:06:59.161 --> 00:07:02.120
or even systems of government.

176
00:07:02.120 --> 00:07:02.121


177
00:07:02.121 --> 00:07:07.160
But we do expect all nations to uphold these two core sovereign duties:

178
00:07:07.160 --> 00:07:07.161


179
00:07:07.161 --> 00:07:16.080
to respect the interests of their own people and the rights of every other sovereign nation.

180
00:07:16.080 --> 00:07:16.081


181
00:07:16.081 --> 00:07:20.640
This is the beautiful vision of this institution,

182
00:07:20.640 --> 00:07:20.641


183
00:07:20.641 --> 00:07:25.080
and this is foundation for cooperation and success.

184
00:07:25.080 --> 00:07:25.081


185
00:07:25.081 --> 00:07:27.080
Strong,

186
00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:27.081


187
00:07:27.081 --> 00:07:32.200
sovereign nations let diverse countries with different values,

188
00:07:32.200 --> 00:07:32.201


189
00:07:32.201 --> 00:07:33.640
different cultures,

190
00:07:33.640 --> 00:07:33.641


191
00:07:33.641 --> 00:07:37.880
and different dreams not just coexist,

192
00:07:37.880 --> 00:07:37.881


193
00:07:37.881 --> 00:07:43.080
but work side by side on the basis of mutual respect.

194
00:07:43.080 --> 00:07:43.081


195
00:07:43.081 --> 00:07:43.640
Strong,

196
00:07:43.640 --> 00:07:43.641


197
00:07:43.641 --> 00:07:51.800
sovereign nations let their people take ownership of the future and control their own destiny.

198
00:07:51.800 --> 00:07:51.801


199
00:07:51.801 --> 00:07:52.800
And strong,

200
00:07:52.800 --> 00:07:52.801


201
00:07:52.801 --> 00:08:02.080
sovereign nations allow individuals to flourish in the fullness of the life intended by God.

202
00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:02.081


203
00:08:02.081 --> 00:08:02.680
In America,

204
00:08:02.680 --> 00:08:02.681


205
00:08:02.681 --> 00:08:07.960
we do not seek to impose our way of life on anyone,

206
00:08:07.960 --> 00:08:07.961


207
00:08:07.961 --> 00:08:12.920
but rather to let it shine as an example for everyone to watch.

208
00:08:12.920 --> 00:08:12.921


209
00:08:12.921 --> 00:08:21.320
This week gives our country a special reason to take pride in that example.

210
00:08:21.320 --> 00:08:21.321


211
00:08:21.321 --> 00:08:28.760
We are celebrating the 230th anniversary of our beloved Constitution --

212
00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:28.761


213
00:08:28.761 --> 00:08:34.600
the oldest constitution still in use in the world today.

214
00:08:34.600 --> 00:08:34.601


215
00:08:34.601 --> 00:08:38.240
This timeless document has been the foundation of peace,

216
00:08:38.240 --> 00:08:38.241


217
00:08:38.241 --> 00:08:39.600
prosperity,

218
00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:39.601


219
00:08:39.601 --> 00:08:49.560
and freedom for the Americans and for countless millions around the globe whose own countries have found inspiration in its respect for human nature,

220
00:08:49.560 --> 00:08:49.561


221
00:08:49.561 --> 00:08:50.280
human dignity,

222
00:08:50.280 --> 00:08:50.281


223
00:08:50.281 --> 00:08:51.840
and the rule of law.

224
00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:51.841


225
00:08:51.841 --> 00:09:00.760
The greatest in the United States Constitution is its first three beautiful words.

226
00:09:00.760 --> 00:09:00.761


227
00:09:00.761 --> 00:09:05.320
They are: “We the people.”

228
00:09:05.320 --> 00:09:05.321


229
00:09:05.321 --> 00:09:10.720
Generations of Americans have sacrificed to maintain the promise of those words,

230
00:09:10.720 --> 00:09:10.721


231
00:09:10.721 --> 00:09:14.240
the promise of our country,

232
00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:14.241


233
00:09:14.241 --> 00:09:16.840
and of our great history.

234
00:09:17.960 --> 00:09:18.041


235
00:09:18.041 --> 00:09:19.600
In America,

236
00:09:19.600 --> 00:09:19.601


237
00:09:19.601 --> 00:09:21.320
the people govern,

238
00:09:21.320 --> 00:09:21.321


239
00:09:21.321 --> 00:09:22.800
the people rule,

240
00:09:22.800 --> 00:09:22.801


241
00:09:22.801 --> 00:09:25.560
and the people are sovereign.

242
00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:25.561


243
00:09:25.561 --> 00:09:28.560
I was elected not to take power,

244
00:09:28.560 --> 00:09:28.561


245
00:09:28.561 --> 00:09:31.280
but to give power to the American people,

246
00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:31.281


247
00:09:31.281 --> 00:09:33.080
where it belongs.

248
00:09:33.080 --> 00:09:33.081


249
00:09:33.081 --> 00:09:34.200
In foreign affairs,

250
00:09:34.200 --> 00:09:34.201


251
00:09:34.201 --> 00:09:38.240
we are renewing this founding principle of sovereignty.

252
00:09:38.240 --> 00:09:38.241


253
00:09:38.241 --> 00:09:41.480
Our government's first duty is to its people,

254
00:09:41.480 --> 00:09:41.481


255
00:09:41.481 --> 00:09:42.840
to our citizens --

256
00:09:42.840 --> 00:09:42.841


257
00:09:42.841 --> 00:09:44.880
to serve their needs,

258
00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:44.881


259
00:09:44.881 --> 00:09:46.240
to ensure their safety,

260
00:09:46.240 --> 00:09:46.241


261
00:09:46.241 --> 00:09:48.080
to preserve their rights,

262
00:09:48.080 --> 00:09:48.081


263
00:09:48.081 --> 00:09:51.200
and to defend their values.

264
00:09:51.200 --> 00:09:51.201


265
00:09:51.201 --> 00:09:53.240
As President of the United States,

266
00:09:53.240 --> 00:09:53.680


267
00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:57.240
I will always put America first,

268
00:09:57.240 --> 00:09:57.241


269
00:09:57.241 --> 00:09:58.320
just like you,

270
00:09:58.320 --> 00:09:58.321


271
00:09:58.321 --> 00:10:02.240
as the leaders of your countries will always,

272
00:10:02.240 --> 00:10:02.400


273
00:10:02.400 --> 00:10:04.160
and should always,

274
00:10:04.160 --> 00:10:04.161


275
00:10:04.161 --> 00:10:13.320
put your countries first.

276
00:10:13.320 --> 00:10:13.321


277
00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:18.400
All responsible leaders have an obligation to serve their own citizens,

278
00:10:18.400 --> 00:10:18.401


279
00:10:18.401 --> 00:10:26.360
and the nation-state remains the best vehicle for elevating the human condition.

280
00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:26.361


281
00:10:26.361 --> 00:10:40.560
But making a better life for our people also requires us to work together in close harmony and unity to create a more safe and peaceful future for all people.

282
00:10:40.560 --> 00:10:40.561


283
00:10:40.561 --> 00:10:45.400
The United States will forever be a great friend to the world,

284
00:10:45.400 --> 00:10:45.401


285
00:10:45.401 --> 00:10:48.800
and especially to its allies.

286
00:10:48.800 --> 00:10:48.801


287
00:10:48.801 --> 00:10:51.600
But we can no longer be taken advantage of,

288
00:10:51.600 --> 00:10:51.601


289
00:10:51.601 --> 00:10:58.720
or enter into a one-sided deal where the United States gets nothing in return.

290
00:10:58.720 --> 00:10:58.721


291
00:10:58.721 --> 00:11:00.760
As long as I hold this office,

292
00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:00.761


293
00:11:00.761 --> 00:11:05.640
I will defend America’s interests above all else.

294
00:11:05.640 --> 00:11:05.641


295
00:11:05.641 --> 00:11:09.480
But in fulfilling our obligations to our own nations,

296
00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:09.481


297
00:11:09.481 --> 00:11:17.440
we also realize that it’s in everyone’s interest to seek a future where all nations can be sovereign,

298
00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:17.441


299
00:11:17.441 --> 00:11:18.400
prosperous,

300
00:11:18.400 --> 00:11:18.401


301
00:11:18.401 --> 00:11:20.400
and secure.

302
00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:20.401


303
00:11:20.401 --> 00:11:27.920
America does more than speak for the values expressed in the United Nations Charter.

304
00:11:27.920 --> 00:11:27.921


305
00:11:27.921 --> 00:11:39.000
Our citizens have paid the ultimate price to defend our freedom and the freedom of many nations represented in this great hall.

306
00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:39.001


307
00:11:39.001 --> 00:11:49.280
America's devotion is measured on the battlefields where our young men and women have fought and sacrificed alongside of our allies,

308
00:11:49.280 --> 00:11:49.281


309
00:11:49.281 --> 00:11:57.920
from the beaches of Europe to the deserts of the Middle East to the jungles of Asia.

310
00:11:57.920 --> 00:11:57.921


311
00:11:57.921 --> 00:12:09.560
It is an eternal credit to the American character that even after we and our allies emerged victorious from the bloodiest war in history,

312
00:12:09.560 --> 00:12:09.561


313
00:12:09.561 --> 00:12:12.840
we did not seek territorial expansion,

314
00:12:12.840 --> 00:12:12.841


315
00:12:12.841 --> 00:12:20.440
or attempt to oppose and impose our way of life on others.

316
00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:20.441


317
00:12:20.441 --> 00:12:21.000
Instead,

318
00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:21.001


319
00:12:21.001 --> 00:12:26.840
we helped build institutions such as this one to defend the sovereignty,

320
00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:26.841


321
00:12:26.841 --> 00:12:28.640
security,

322
00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:28.641


323
00:12:28.641 --> 00:12:31.400
and prosperity for all.

324
00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:31.401


325
00:12:31.401 --> 00:12:34.840
For the diverse nations of the world,

326
00:12:34.840 --> 00:12:34.841


327
00:12:34.841 --> 00:12:37.440
this is our hope.

328
00:12:37.440 --> 00:12:37.441


329
00:12:37.441 --> 00:12:39.120
We want harmony and friendship,

330
00:12:39.120 --> 00:12:39.121


331
00:12:39.121 --> 00:12:41.240
not conflict and strife.

332
00:12:42.320 --> 00:12:42.401


333
00:12:42.401 --> 00:12:44.200
We are guided by outcomes,

334
00:12:44.200 --> 00:12:44.201


335
00:12:44.201 --> 00:12:46.520
not ideology.

336
00:12:46.520 --> 00:12:46.521


337
00:12:46.521 --> 00:12:50.280
We have a policy of principled realism,

338
00:12:50.280 --> 00:12:50.281


339
00:12:50.281 --> 00:12:52.160
rooted in shared goals,

340
00:12:52.160 --> 00:12:52.161


341
00:12:52.161 --> 00:12:52.840
interests,

342
00:12:52.840 --> 00:12:52.880


343
00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:54.120
and values.

344
00:12:54.120 --> 00:12:54.121


345
00:12:54.121 --> 00:13:01.800
That realism forces us to confront a question facing every leader and nation in this room.

346
00:13:02.640 --> 00:13:02.721


347
00:13:02.721 --> 00:13:06.120
It is a question we cannot escape or avoid.

348
00:13:06.120 --> 00:13:06.121


349
00:13:06.121 --> 00:13:08.960
We will slide down the path of complacency,

350
00:13:08.960 --> 00:13:08.961


351
00:13:08.961 --> 00:13:10.960
numb to the challenges,

352
00:13:10.960 --> 00:13:11.000


353
00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:11.440
threats,

354
00:13:11.440 --> 00:13:11.441


355
00:13:11.441 --> 00:13:15.120
and even wars that we face.

356
00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:15.121


357
00:13:15.121 --> 00:13:20.040
Or do we have enough strength and pride to confront those dangers today,

358
00:13:20.040 --> 00:13:20.041


359
00:13:20.041 --> 00:13:26.400
so that our citizens can enjoy peace and prosperity tomorrow?

360
00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:26.401


361
00:13:26.401 --> 00:13:30.120
If we desire to lift up our citizens,

362
00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:30.121


363
00:13:30.121 --> 00:13:34.520
if we aspire to the approval of history,

364
00:13:34.520 --> 00:13:34.521


365
00:13:34.521 --> 00:13:41.760
then we must fulfill our sovereign duties to the people we faithfully represent.

366
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:41.761


367
00:13:41.761 --> 00:13:44.600
We must protect our nations,

368
00:13:44.600 --> 00:13:44.601


369
00:13:44.601 --> 00:13:46.800
their interests,

370
00:13:46.800 --> 00:13:46.801


371
00:13:46.801 --> 00:13:48.320
and their futures.

372
00:13:48.320 --> 00:13:48.321


373
00:13:48.321 --> 00:13:52.400
We must reject threats to sovereignty,

374
00:13:52.400 --> 00:13:52.401


375
00:13:52.401 --> 00:13:56.880
from the Ukraine to the South China Sea.

376
00:13:56.880 --> 00:13:56.881


377
00:13:56.881 --> 00:13:59.400
We must uphold respect for law,

378
00:13:59.400 --> 00:13:59.401


379
00:13:59.401 --> 00:14:01.600
respect for borders,

380
00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:01.601


381
00:14:01.601 --> 00:14:04.120
and respect for culture,

382
00:14:04.120 --> 00:14:04.121


383
00:14:04.121 --> 00:14:07.480
and the peaceful engagement these allow.

384
00:14:08.600 --> 00:14:08.681


385
00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:11.960
And just as the founders of this body intended,

386
00:14:12.840 --> 00:14:12.921


387
00:14:12.921 --> 00:14:20.320
we must work together and confront together those who threaten us with chaos,

388
00:14:20.320 --> 00:14:20.321


389
00:14:20.321 --> 00:14:21.680
turmoil,

390
00:14:21.680 --> 00:14:21.681


391
00:14:21.681 --> 00:14:24.440
and terror.

392
00:14:24.440 --> 00:14:24.441


393
00:14:24.441 --> 00:14:33.640
The scourge of our planet today is a small group of rogue regimes that violate every principle on which the United Nations is based.

394
00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:33.641


395
00:14:33.641 --> 00:14:41.680
They respect neither their own citizens nor the sovereign rights of their countries.

396
00:14:41.680 --> 00:14:41.681


397
00:14:41.681 --> 00:14:46.960
If the righteous many do not confront the wicked few,

398
00:14:46.960 --> 00:14:46.961


399
00:14:46.961 --> 00:14:50.920
then evil will triumph.

400
00:14:50.920 --> 00:14:50.921


401
00:14:50.921 --> 00:14:55.320
When decent people and nations become bystanders to history,

402
00:14:55.320 --> 00:14:55.321


403
00:14:55.321 --> 00:15:00.920
the forces of destruction only gather power and strength.

404
00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:00.921


405
00:15:00.921 --> 00:15:12.280
No one has shown more contempt for other nations and for the wellbeing of their own people than the depraved regime in North Korea.

406
00:15:12.280 --> 00:15:12.281


407
00:15:12.281 --> 00:15:17.160
It is responsible for the starvation deaths of millions of North Koreans,

408
00:15:17.160 --> 00:15:17.200


409
00:15:17.200 --> 00:15:19.600
and for the imprisonment,

410
00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:19.960


411
00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:20.400
torture,

412
00:15:20.400 --> 00:15:20.560


413
00:15:20.560 --> 00:15:20.880
killing,

414
00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:20.960


415
00:15:20.960 --> 00:15:24.680
and oppression of countless more.

416
00:15:24.680 --> 00:15:24.681


417
00:15:24.681 --> 00:15:32.600
We were all witness to the regime's deadly abuse when an innocent American college student,

418
00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:32.601


419
00:15:32.601 --> 00:15:33.480
Otto Warmbier,

420
00:15:33.480 --> 00:15:33.520


421
00:15:33.520 --> 00:15:39.800
was returned to America only to die a few days later.

422
00:15:39.800 --> 00:15:39.801


423
00:15:39.801 --> 00:15:50.320
We saw it in the assassination of the dictator's brother using banned nerve agents in an international airport.

424
00:15:51.640 --> 00:15:51.721


425
00:15:51.721 --> 00:16:06.160
We know it kidnapped a sweet 13-year-old Japanese girl from a beach in her own country to enslave her as a language tutor for North Korea's spies.

426
00:16:06.160 --> 00:16:06.161


427
00:16:06.161 --> 00:16:07.840
If this is not twisted enough,

428
00:16:07.840 --> 00:16:07.841


429
00:16:07.841 --> 00:16:19.960
now North Korea's reckless pursuit of nuclear weapons and ballistic missiles threatens the entire world with unthinkable loss of human life.

430
00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:19.961


431
00:16:19.961 --> 00:16:23.800
It is an outrage that some nations would not only trade with such a regime,

432
00:16:23.800 --> 00:16:23.801


433
00:16:23.801 --> 00:16:25.640
but would arm,

434
00:16:25.640 --> 00:16:25.680


435
00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:26.320
supply,

436
00:16:26.320 --> 00:16:26.360


437
00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:34.720
and financially support a country that imperils the world with nuclear conflict.

438
00:16:34.720 --> 00:16:34.721


439
00:16:34.721 --> 00:16:43.480
No nation on earth has an interest in seeing this band of criminals arm itself with nuclear weapons and missiles.

440
00:16:43.480 --> 00:16:43.481


441
00:16:43.481 --> 00:16:47.480
The United States has great strength and patience,

442
00:16:47.480 --> 00:16:47.481


443
00:16:47.481 --> 00:16:49.920
but if it is forced to defend itself or its allies,

444
00:16:49.920 --> 00:16:49.921


445
00:16:49.921 --> 00:16:56.840
we will have no choice but to totally destroy North Korea.

446
00:16:56.840 --> 00:16:56.841


447
00:16:56.841 --> 00:17:03.680
Rocket Man is on a suicide mission for himself and for his regime.

448
00:17:03.680 --> 00:17:03.681


449
00:17:03.681 --> 00:17:05.320
The United States is ready,

450
00:17:05.320 --> 00:17:05.321


451
00:17:05.321 --> 00:17:07.840
willing and able,

452
00:17:07.840 --> 00:17:07.841


453
00:17:07.841 --> 00:17:11.560
but hopefully this will not be necessary.

454
00:17:11.560 --> 00:17:11.561


455
00:17:11.561 --> 00:17:16.640
That’s what the United Nations is all about;

456
00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:16.641


457
00:17:16.641 --> 00:17:20.280
that’s what the United Nations is for.

458
00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:21.081


459
00:17:21.081 --> 00:17:22.640
Let’s see how they do.

460
00:17:23.720 --> 00:17:23.801


461
00:17:23.801 --> 00:17:33.640
It is time for North Korea to realize that the denuclearization is its only acceptable future.

462
00:17:33.640 --> 00:17:33.641


463
00:17:33.641 --> 00:17:43.720
The United Nations Security Council recently held two unanimous 15-0 votes adopting hard-hitting resolutions against North Korea,

464
00:17:43.720 --> 00:17:43.760


465
00:17:43.760 --> 00:17:49.960
and I want to thank China and Russia for joining the vote to impose sanctions,

466
00:17:49.960 --> 00:17:49.961


467
00:17:49.961 --> 00:17:53.920
along with all of the other members of the Security Council.

468
00:17:54.760 --> 00:17:54.841


469
00:17:54.841 --> 00:17:57.360
Thank you to all involved.

470
00:17:57.360 --> 00:17:57.361


471
00:17:57.361 --> 00:18:00.760
But we must do much more.

472
00:18:00.760 --> 00:18:00.761


473
00:18:00.761 --> 00:18:09.560
It is time for all nations to work together to isolate the Kim regime until it ceases its hostile behavior.

474
00:18:09.560 --> 00:18:09.561


475
00:18:09.561 --> 00:18:13.520
We face this decision not only in North Korea.

476
00:18:14.400 --> 00:18:14.481


477
00:18:14.481 --> 00:18:20.080
It is far past time for the nations of the world to confront another reckless regime --

478
00:18:20.080 --> 00:18:20.081


479
00:18:20.081 --> 00:18:22.360
one that speaks openly of mass murder,

480
00:18:22.360 --> 00:18:22.361


481
00:18:22.361 --> 00:18:25.200
vowing death to America,

482
00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:25.201


483
00:18:25.201 --> 00:18:27.440
destruction to Israel,

484
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:27.441


485
00:18:27.441 --> 00:18:32.320
and ruin for many leaders and nations in this room.

486
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:32.321


487
00:18:32.321 --> 00:18:40.960
The Iranian government masks a corrupt dictatorship behind the false guise of a democracy.

488
00:18:40.960 --> 00:18:40.961


489
00:18:40.961 --> 00:18:53.480
It has turned a wealthy country with a rich history and culture into an economically depleted rogue state whose chief exports are violence,

490
00:18:53.480 --> 00:18:53.481


491
00:18:53.481 --> 00:18:53.640
bloodshed,

492
00:18:53.640 --> 00:18:53.641


493
00:18:53.641 --> 00:18:55.120
and chaos.

494
00:18:55.120 --> 00:18:55.121


495
00:18:55.121 --> 00:18:59.040
The longest-suffering victims of Iran's leaders are,

496
00:18:59.040 --> 00:18:59.041


497
00:18:59.041 --> 00:19:00.800
in fact,

498
00:19:00.800 --> 00:19:00.801


499
00:19:00.801 --> 00:19:03.400
its own people.

500
00:19:03.400 --> 00:19:03.401


501
00:19:03.401 --> 00:19:07.880
Rather than use its resources to improve Iranian lives,

502
00:19:07.880 --> 00:19:07.920


503
00:19:07.920 --> 00:19:21.120
its oil profits go to fund Hezbollah and other terrorists that kill innocent Muslims and attack their peaceful Arab and Israeli neighbors.

504
00:19:21.120 --> 00:19:21.121


505
00:19:21.121 --> 00:19:21.440
This wealth,

506
00:19:21.440 --> 00:19:21.441


507
00:19:21.441 --> 00:19:24.560
which rightly belongs to Iran's people,

508
00:19:24.560 --> 00:19:24.561


509
00:19:24.561 --> 00:19:30.200
also goes to shore up Bashar al-Assad's dictatorship,

510
00:19:30.200 --> 00:19:30.201


511
00:19:30.201 --> 00:19:32.480
fuel Yemen's civil war,

512
00:19:32.480 --> 00:19:32.520


513
00:19:32.520 --> 00:19:38.960
and undermine peace throughout the entire Middle East.

514
00:19:38.960 --> 00:19:38.961


515
00:19:38.961 --> 00:19:49.120
We cannot let a murderous regime continue these destabilizing activities while building dangerous missiles,

516
00:19:49.120 --> 00:19:49.121


517
00:19:49.121 --> 00:19:59.400
and we cannot abide by an agreement if it provides cover for the eventual construction of a nuclear program.

518
00:19:59.400 --> 00:19:59.401


519
00:19:59.401 --> 00:20:17.560
(Applause.) The Iran Deal was one of the worst and most one-sided transactions the United States has ever entered into.

520
00:20:17.560 --> 00:20:17.561


521
00:20:17.561 --> 00:20:17.880
Frankly,

522
00:20:17.880 --> 00:20:17.920


523
00:20:17.920 --> 00:20:21.480
that deal is an embarrassment to the United States,

524
00:20:21.480 --> 00:20:21.481


525
00:20:21.481 --> 00:20:25.000
and I don’t think you’ve heard the last of it --

526
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:25.001


527
00:20:25.001 --> 00:20:27.760
believe me.

528
00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:27.761


529
00:20:27.761 --> 00:20:37.800
It is time for the entire world to join us in demanding that Iran's government end its pursuit of death and destruction.

530
00:20:37.800 --> 00:20:37.801


531
00:20:37.801 --> 00:20:46.360
It is time for the regime to free all Americans and citizens of other nations that they have unjustly detained.

532
00:20:46.360 --> 00:20:47.040


533
00:20:47.040 --> 00:20:47.480
And above all,

534
00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:47.481


535
00:20:47.481 --> 00:20:51.200
Iran's government must stop supporting terrorists,

536
00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:51.201


537
00:20:51.201 --> 00:20:53.280
begin serving its own people,

538
00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:53.281


539
00:20:53.281 --> 00:20:58.840
and respect the sovereign rights of its neighbors.

540
00:20:58.840 --> 00:20:58.841


541
00:20:58.841 --> 00:21:02.880
The entire world understands that the good people of Iran want change,

542
00:21:02.880 --> 00:21:02.881


543
00:21:02.881 --> 00:21:03.760
and,

544
00:21:03.760 --> 00:21:03.761


545
00:21:03.761 --> 00:21:07.400
other than the vast military power of the United States,

546
00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:07.401


547
00:21:07.401 --> 00:21:15.120
that Iran's people are what their leaders fear the most.

548
00:21:15.120 --> 00:21:15.121


549
00:21:15.121 --> 00:21:19.760
This is what causes the regime to restrict Internet access,

550
00:21:19.760 --> 00:21:20.760


551
00:21:20.760 --> 00:21:22.600
tear down satellite dishes,

552
00:21:22.600 --> 00:21:22.601


553
00:21:22.601 --> 00:21:25.840
shoot unarmed student protestors,

554
00:21:25.840 --> 00:21:25.841


555
00:21:25.841 --> 00:21:30.640
and imprison political reformers.

556
00:21:30.640 --> 00:21:30.641


557
00:21:30.641 --> 00:21:33.520
Oppressive regimes cannot endure forever,

558
00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:33.521


559
00:21:33.521 --> 00:21:38.640
and the day will come when the Iranian people will face a choice.

560
00:21:38.640 --> 00:21:38.641


561
00:21:38.641 --> 00:21:42.400
Will they continue down the path of poverty,

562
00:21:42.400 --> 00:21:42.401


563
00:21:42.401 --> 00:21:43.200
bloodshed,

564
00:21:43.200 --> 00:21:43.201


565
00:21:43.201 --> 00:21:52.320
and terror? Or will the Iranian people return to the nation's proud roots as a center of civilization,

566
00:21:52.320 --> 00:21:52.321


567
00:21:52.321 --> 00:21:53.280
culture,

568
00:21:53.280 --> 00:21:53.320


569
00:21:53.320 --> 00:22:01.080
and wealth where their people can be happy and prosperous once again?

570
00:22:01.080 --> 00:22:01.081


571
00:22:01.081 --> 00:22:12.320
The Iranian regime's support for terror is in stark contrast to the recent commitments of many of its neighbors to fight terrorism and halt its financing.

572
00:22:12.320 --> 00:22:12.321


573
00:22:12.321 --> 00:22:14.800
In Saudi Arabia early last year,

574
00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:14.801


575
00:22:14.801 --> 00:22:25.760
I was greatly honored to address the leaders of more than 50 Arab and Muslim nations.

576
00:22:25.760 --> 00:22:25.761


577
00:22:25.761 --> 00:22:36.520
We agreed that all responsible nations must work together to confront terrorists and the Islamist extremism that inspires them.

578
00:22:36.520 --> 00:22:36.521


579
00:22:36.521 --> 00:22:44.200
We will stop radical Islamic terrorism because we cannot allow it to tear up our nation,

580
00:22:44.200 --> 00:22:44.240


581
00:22:44.240 --> 00:22:48.640
and indeed to tear up the entire world.

582
00:22:48.640 --> 00:22:48.641


583
00:22:48.641 --> 00:22:51.920
We must deny the terrorists safe haven,

584
00:22:51.920 --> 00:22:51.921


585
00:22:51.921 --> 00:22:53.360
transit,

586
00:22:53.360 --> 00:22:53.400


587
00:22:53.400 --> 00:22:54.360
funding,

588
00:22:54.360 --> 00:22:54.361


589
00:22:54.361 --> 00:23:00.000
and any form of support for their vile and sinister ideology.

590
00:23:01.040 --> 00:23:01.121


591
00:23:01.121 --> 00:23:04.480
We must drive them out of our nations.

592
00:23:04.480 --> 00:23:04.481


593
00:23:04.481 --> 00:23:13.960
It is time to expose and hold responsible those countries who support and finance terror groups like al Qaeda,

594
00:23:13.960 --> 00:23:14.080


595
00:23:14.920 --> 00:23:15.240
Hezbollah,

596
00:23:15.240 --> 00:23:15.280


597
00:23:15.280 --> 00:23:21.160
the Taliban and others that slaughter innocent people.

598
00:23:21.160 --> 00:23:21.161


599
00:23:21.161 --> 00:23:37.120
The United States and our allies are working together throughout the Middle East to crush the loser terrorists and stop the reemergence of safe havens they use to launch attacks on all of our people.

600
00:23:37.120 --> 00:23:37.121


601
00:23:37.121 --> 00:23:37.680
Last month,

602
00:23:37.680 --> 00:23:37.681


603
00:23:37.681 --> 00:23:45.080
I announced a new strategy for victory in the fight against this evil in Afghanistan.

604
00:23:46.280 --> 00:23:46.440


605
00:23:46.440 --> 00:23:46.800
From now on,

606
00:23:46.800 --> 00:23:46.801


607
00:23:46.801 --> 00:23:52.080
our security interests will dictate the length and scope of military operations,

608
00:23:52.080 --> 00:23:52.081


609
00:23:52.081 --> 00:23:58.000
not arbitrary benchmarks and timetables set up by politicians.

610
00:23:58.000 --> 00:23:58.040


611
00:23:58.040 --> 00:24:09.720
I have also totally changed the rules of engagement in our fight against the Taliban and other terrorist groups.

612
00:24:09.720 --> 00:24:09.721


613
00:24:09.721 --> 00:24:10.320
In Syria and Iraq,

614
00:24:10.320 --> 00:24:10.321


615
00:24:10.321 --> 00:24:15.680
we have made big gains toward lasting defeat of ISIS.

616
00:24:15.680 --> 00:24:15.681


617
00:24:15.681 --> 00:24:16.920
In fact,

618
00:24:16.920 --> 00:24:16.921


619
00:24:16.921 --> 00:24:24.480
our country has achieved more against ISIS in the last eight months than it has in many,

620
00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:24.560


621
00:24:24.560 --> 00:24:27.680
many years combined.

622
00:24:27.680 --> 00:24:27.681


623
00:24:27.681 --> 00:24:33.960
We seek the de-escalation of the Syrian conflict,

624
00:24:33.960 --> 00:24:33.961


625
00:24:33.961 --> 00:24:38.680
and a political solution that honors the will of the Syrian people.

626
00:24:38.680 --> 00:24:38.681


627
00:24:38.681 --> 00:24:43.840
The actions of the criminal regime of Bashar al-Assad,

628
00:24:43.840 --> 00:24:43.841


629
00:24:43.841 --> 00:24:48.240
including the use of chemical weapons against his own citizens --

630
00:24:48.240 --> 00:24:48.241


631
00:24:48.241 --> 00:24:50.480
even innocent children --

632
00:24:50.480 --> 00:24:50.481


633
00:24:50.481 --> 00:24:56.360
shock the conscience of every decent person.

634
00:24:56.360 --> 00:24:56.361


635
00:24:56.361 --> 00:25:02.640
No society can be safe if banned chemical weapons are allowed to spread.

636
00:25:02.640 --> 00:25:02.641


637
00:25:02.641 --> 00:25:13.520
That is why the United States carried out a missile strike on the airbase that launched the attack.

638
00:25:13.520 --> 00:25:13.560


639
00:25:13.560 --> 00:25:23.280
We appreciate the efforts of United Nations agencies that are providing vital humanitarian assistance in areas liberated from ISIS,

640
00:25:23.280 --> 00:25:23.281


641
00:25:23.281 --> 00:25:26.280
and we especially thank Jordan,

642
00:25:26.280 --> 00:25:26.320


643
00:25:26.320 --> 00:25:36.640
Turkey and Lebanon for their role in hosting refugees from the Syrian conflict.

644
00:25:36.640 --> 00:25:36.641


645
00:25:36.641 --> 00:25:46.760
The United States is a compassionate nation and has spent billions and billions of dollars in helping to support this effort.

646
00:25:46.760 --> 00:25:47.960


647
00:25:47.960 --> 00:25:55.400
We seek an approach to refugee resettlement that is designed to help these horribly treated people,

648
00:25:55.400 --> 00:25:55.401


649
00:25:55.401 --> 00:25:59.960
and which enables their eventual return to their home countries,

650
00:25:59.960 --> 00:25:59.961


651
00:25:59.961 --> 00:26:03.600
to be part of the rebuilding process.

652
00:26:03.600 --> 00:26:03.601


653
00:26:03.601 --> 00:26:11.200
For the cost of resettling one refugee in the United States,

654
00:26:11.200 --> 00:26:11.201


655
00:26:11.201 --> 00:26:14.600
we can assist more than 10 in their home region.

656
00:26:14.600 --> 00:26:14.601


657
00:26:14.601 --> 00:26:17.160
Out of the goodness of our hearts,

658
00:26:17.160 --> 00:26:17.200


659
00:26:17.200 --> 00:26:21.040
we offer financial assistance to hosting countries in the region,

660
00:26:21.040 --> 00:26:21.041


661
00:26:21.041 --> 00:26:31.720
and we support recent agreements of the G20 nations that will seek to host refugees as close to their home countries as possible.

662
00:26:33.120 --> 00:26:33.201


663
00:26:33.201 --> 00:26:33.880
This is the safe,

664
00:26:33.880 --> 00:26:33.881


665
00:26:33.881 --> 00:26:35.560
responsible,

666
00:26:35.560 --> 00:26:35.561


667
00:26:35.561 --> 00:26:39.480
and humanitarian approach.

668
00:26:39.480 --> 00:26:39.520


669
00:26:39.520 --> 00:26:40.040
For decades,

670
00:26:40.040 --> 00:26:40.041


671
00:26:40.041 --> 00:26:46.440
the United States has dealt with migration challenges here in the Western Hemisphere.

672
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:46.441


673
00:26:46.441 --> 00:26:47.000
We have learned that,

674
00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:47.001


675
00:26:47.001 --> 00:26:48.000
over the long term,

676
00:26:48.000 --> 00:26:48.001


677
00:26:48.001 --> 00:26:56.600
uncontrolled migration is deeply unfair to both the sending and the receiving countries.

678
00:26:56.600 --> 00:26:56.601


679
00:26:56.601 --> 00:26:57.360
For the sending countries,

680
00:26:57.360 --> 00:26:57.640


681
00:26:57.640 --> 00:27:04.040
it reduces domestic pressure to pursue needed political and economic reform,

682
00:27:04.040 --> 00:27:04.080


683
00:27:04.080 --> 00:27:15.080
and drains them of the human capital necessary to motivate and implement those reforms.

684
00:27:15.080 --> 00:27:15.081


685
00:27:15.081 --> 00:27:16.600
For the receiving countries,

686
00:27:16.600 --> 00:27:16.601


687
00:27:16.601 --> 00:27:29.560
the substantial costs of uncontrolled migration are borne overwhelmingly by low-income citizens whose concerns are often ignored by both media and government.

688
00:27:29.560 --> 00:27:29.561


689
00:27:29.561 --> 00:27:40.240
I want to salute the work of the United Nations in seeking to address the problems that cause people to flee from their homes.

690
00:27:40.240 --> 00:27:40.241


691
00:27:40.241 --> 00:27:53.240
The United Nations and African Union led peacekeeping missions to have invaluable contributions in stabilizing conflicts in Africa.

692
00:27:54.280 --> 00:27:54.400


693
00:27:54.400 --> 00:27:58.240
The United States continues to lead the world in humanitarian assistance,

694
00:27:58.240 --> 00:27:58.241


695
00:27:58.241 --> 00:28:03.840
including famine prevention and relief in South Sudan,

696
00:28:03.840 --> 00:28:03.841


697
00:28:03.841 --> 00:28:05.240
Somalia,

698
00:28:05.240 --> 00:28:05.280


699
00:28:05.280 --> 00:28:09.480
and northern Nigeria and Yemen.

700
00:28:09.480 --> 00:28:09.481


701
00:28:09.481 --> 00:28:16.040
We have invested in better health and opportunity all over the world through programs like PEPFAR,

702
00:28:16.040 --> 00:28:16.080


703
00:28:16.080 --> 00:28:18.480
which funds AIDS relief;

704
00:28:18.480 --> 00:28:18.481


705
00:28:18.481 --> 00:28:22.040
the President's Malaria Initiative;

706
00:28:22.040 --> 00:28:22.041


707
00:28:22.041 --> 00:28:25.400
the Global Health Security Agenda;

708
00:28:25.400 --> 00:28:25.480


709
00:28:25.480 --> 00:28:29.920
the Global Fund to End Modern Slavery;

710
00:28:29.920 --> 00:28:30.800


711
00:28:30.800 --> 00:28:34.040
and the Women Entrepreneurs Finance Initiative,

712
00:28:34.040 --> 00:28:34.041


713
00:28:34.041 --> 00:28:41.960
part of our commitment to empowering women all across the globe.

714
00:28:41.960 --> 00:28:42.000


715
00:28:42.000 --> 00:28:48.640
We also thank -- (applause) --

716
00:28:48.640 --> 00:28:48.641


717
00:28:48.641 --> 00:29:02.440
we also thank the Secretary General for recognizing that the United Nations must reform if it is to be an effective partner in confronting threats to sovereignty,

718
00:29:02.440 --> 00:29:02.441


719
00:29:02.441 --> 00:29:04.080
security,

720
00:29:04.080 --> 00:29:04.081


721
00:29:04.081 --> 00:29:05.880
and prosperity.

722
00:29:05.880 --> 00:29:05.881


723
00:29:05.881 --> 00:29:11.320
Too often the focus of this organization has not been on results,

724
00:29:11.320 --> 00:29:11.321


725
00:29:11.321 --> 00:29:14.280
but on bureaucracy and process.

726
00:29:14.280 --> 00:29:14.281


727
00:29:14.281 --> 00:29:15.960
In some cases,

728
00:29:15.960 --> 00:29:15.961


729
00:29:15.961 --> 00:29:26.640
states that seek to subvert this institution's noble aims have hijacked the very systems that are supposed to advance them.

730
00:29:26.640 --> 00:29:26.760


731
00:29:26.760 --> 00:29:28.200
For example,

732
00:29:28.200 --> 00:29:28.201


733
00:29:28.201 --> 00:29:39.760
it is a massive source of embarrassment to the United Nations that some governments with egregious human rights records sit on the U.N.

734
00:29:39.760 --> 00:29:39.761


735
00:29:39.761 --> 00:29:42.360
Human Rights Council.

736
00:29:42.360 --> 00:29:42.361


737
00:29:42.361 --> 00:29:50.240
The United States is one out of 193 countries in the United Nations,

738
00:29:50.240 --> 00:29:50.241


739
00:29:50.241 --> 00:29:55.400
and yet we pay 22 percent of the entire budget and more.

740
00:29:55.400 --> 00:29:55.401


741
00:29:55.401 --> 00:29:56.720
In fact,

742
00:29:56.720 --> 00:29:56.721


743
00:29:56.721 --> 00:30:01.600
we pay far more than anybody realizes.

744
00:30:01.600 --> 00:30:01.601


745
00:30:01.601 --> 00:30:05.000
The United States bears an unfair cost burden,

746
00:30:05.000 --> 00:30:05.001


747
00:30:05.001 --> 00:30:05.440
but,

748
00:30:05.440 --> 00:30:05.441


749
00:30:05.441 --> 00:30:06.880
to be fair,

750
00:30:06.880 --> 00:30:06.920


751
00:30:06.920 --> 00:30:11.560
if it could actually accomplish all of its stated goals,

752
00:30:11.560 --> 00:30:11.561


753
00:30:11.561 --> 00:30:14.200
especially the goal of peace,

754
00:30:14.200 --> 00:30:14.201


755
00:30:14.201 --> 00:30:21.200
this investment would easily be well worth it.

756
00:30:21.200 --> 00:30:21.201


757
00:30:21.201 --> 00:30:25.120
Major portions of the world are in conflict and some,

758
00:30:25.120 --> 00:30:25.121


759
00:30:25.121 --> 00:30:25.680
in fact,

760
00:30:25.680 --> 00:30:25.681


761
00:30:25.681 --> 00:30:27.600
are going to hell.

762
00:30:27.600 --> 00:30:27.601


763
00:30:27.601 --> 00:30:30.680
But the powerful people in this room,

764
00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:30.681


765
00:30:30.681 --> 00:30:34.880
under the guidance and auspices of the United Nations,

766
00:30:34.880 --> 00:30:34.881


767
00:30:34.881 --> 00:30:38.640
can solve many of these vicious and complex problems.

768
00:30:38.640 --> 00:30:38.641


769
00:30:38.641 --> 00:30:54.600
The American people hope that one day soon the United Nations can be a much more accountable and effective advocate for human dignity and freedom around the world.

770
00:30:54.600 --> 00:30:54.601


771
00:30:54.601 --> 00:30:54.720
In the meantime,

772
00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:54.721


773
00:30:54.721 --> 00:31:01.360
we believe that no nation should have to bear a disproportionate share of the burden,

774
00:31:01.360 --> 00:31:01.361


775
00:31:01.361 --> 00:31:03.320
militarily or financially.

776
00:31:03.320 --> 00:31:03.321


777
00:31:03.321 --> 00:31:13.240
Nations of the world must take a greater role in promoting secure and prosperous societies in their own regions.

778
00:31:13.240 --> 00:31:13.241


779
00:31:13.241 --> 00:31:14.800
That is why in the Western Hemisphere,

780
00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:14.840


781
00:31:14.840 --> 00:31:25.600
the United States has stood against the corrupt and destabilizing regime in Cuba and embraced the enduring dream of the Cuban people to live in freedom.

782
00:31:25.600 --> 00:31:25.601


783
00:31:25.601 --> 00:31:39.880
My administration recently announced that we will not lift sanctions on the Cuban government until it makes fundamental reforms.

784
00:31:39.880 --> 00:31:39.881


785
00:31:39.881 --> 00:31:41.800
We have also imposed tough,

786
00:31:41.800 --> 00:31:41.801


787
00:31:41.801 --> 00:31:46.520
calibrated sanctions on the socialist Maduro regime in Venezuela,

788
00:31:46.520 --> 00:31:46.560


789
00:31:46.560 --> 00:31:53.200
which has brought a once thriving nation to the brink of total collapse.

790
00:31:53.200 --> 00:31:53.201


791
00:31:53.201 --> 00:32:04.560
The socialist dictatorship of Nicolas Maduro has inflicted terrible pain and suffering on the good people of that country.

792
00:32:04.560 --> 00:32:04.561


793
00:32:04.561 --> 00:32:17.520
This corrupt regime destroyed a prosperous nation by imposing a failed ideology that has produced poverty and misery everywhere it has been tried.

794
00:32:17.520 --> 00:32:17.640


795
00:32:18.720 --> 00:32:19.440
To make matters worse,

796
00:32:19.440 --> 00:32:19.480


797
00:32:19.480 --> 00:32:22.200
Maduro has defied his own people,

798
00:32:22.200 --> 00:32:22.201


799
00:32:22.201 --> 00:32:30.200
stealing power from their elected representatives to preserve his disastrous rule.

800
00:32:30.200 --> 00:32:30.240


801
00:32:30.240 --> 00:32:36.360
The Venezuelan people are starving and their country is collapsing.

802
00:32:36.360 --> 00:32:36.361


803
00:32:36.361 --> 00:32:40.760
Their democratic institutions are being destroyed.

804
00:32:40.760 --> 00:32:40.880


805
00:32:41.720 --> 00:32:47.280
This situation is completely unacceptable and we cannot stand by and watch.

806
00:32:47.280 --> 00:32:47.281


807
00:32:47.281 --> 00:32:51.040
As a responsible neighbor and friend,

808
00:32:51.040 --> 00:32:51.041


809
00:32:51.041 --> 00:32:55.800
we and all others have a goal.

810
00:32:55.800 --> 00:32:55.801


811
00:32:55.801 --> 00:33:00.680
That goal is to help them regain their freedom,

812
00:33:00.680 --> 00:33:00.720


813
00:33:00.720 --> 00:33:02.520
recover their country,

814
00:33:02.520 --> 00:33:02.521


815
00:33:02.521 --> 00:33:05.880
and restore their democracy.

816
00:33:05.880 --> 00:33:05.881


817
00:33:05.881 --> 00:33:16.040
I would like to thank leaders in this room for condemning the regime and providing vital support to the Venezuelan people.

818
00:33:16.040 --> 00:33:16.041


819
00:33:16.041 --> 00:33:23.000
The United States has taken important steps to hold the regime accountable.

820
00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:23.001


821
00:33:23.001 --> 00:33:33.720
We are prepared to take further action if the government of Venezuela persists on its path to impose authoritarian rule on the Venezuelan people.

822
00:33:33.720 --> 00:33:33.721


823
00:33:33.721 --> 00:33:44.760
We are fortunate to have incredibly strong and healthy trade relationships with many of the Latin American countries gathered here today.

824
00:33:44.760 --> 00:33:44.800


825
00:33:44.800 --> 00:33:55.480
Our economic bond forms a critical foundation for advancing peace and prosperity for all of our people and all of our neighbors.

826
00:33:55.480 --> 00:33:55.481


827
00:33:55.481 --> 00:34:07.280
I ask every country represented here today to be prepared to do more to address this very real crisis.

828
00:34:07.280 --> 00:34:07.320


829
00:34:07.320 --> 00:34:21.480
We call for the full restoration of democracy and political freedoms in Venezuela.

830
00:34:21.480 --> 00:34:21.520


831
00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:22.440
(Applause.)

832
00:34:22.440 --> 00:34:22.441


833
00:34:22.441 --> 00:34:27.480
The problem in Venezuela is not that socialism has been poorly implemented,

834
00:34:27.480 --> 00:34:27.481


835
00:34:27.481 --> 00:34:30.760
but that socialism has been faithfully implemented.

836
00:34:30.760 --> 00:34:30.761


837
00:34:30.761 --> 00:34:45.040
(Applause.) From the Soviet Union to Cuba to Venezuela,

838
00:34:45.040 --> 00:34:45.120


839
00:34:45.120 --> 00:34:49.640
wherever true socialism or communism has been adopted,

840
00:34:49.640 --> 00:34:49.760


841
00:34:50.560 --> 00:34:53.800
it has delivered anguish and devastation and failure.

842
00:34:53.800 --> 00:34:53.840


843
00:34:53.840 --> 00:35:06.240
Those who preach the tenets of these discredited ideologies only contribute to the continued suffering of the people who live under these cruel systems.

844
00:35:06.240 --> 00:35:06.241


845
00:35:06.241 --> 00:35:12.080
America stands with every person living under a brutal regime.

846
00:35:12.080 --> 00:35:12.081


847
00:35:12.081 --> 00:35:17.520
Our respect for sovereignty is also a call for action.

848
00:35:17.520 --> 00:35:17.521


849
00:35:17.521 --> 00:35:22.040
All people deserve a government that cares for their safety,

850
00:35:22.040 --> 00:35:22.080


851
00:35:22.080 --> 00:35:23.240
their interests,

852
00:35:23.240 --> 00:35:23.241


853
00:35:23.241 --> 00:35:24.160
and their wellbeing,

854
00:35:24.160 --> 00:35:24.161


855
00:35:24.161 --> 00:35:28.240
including their prosperity.

856
00:35:28.240 --> 00:35:28.241


857
00:35:28.241 --> 00:35:28.360
In America,

858
00:35:28.360 --> 00:35:28.361


859
00:35:28.361 --> 00:35:33.280
we seek stronger ties of business and trade with all nations of good will,

860
00:35:33.280 --> 00:35:33.281


861
00:35:33.281 --> 00:35:38.560
but this trade must be fair and it must be reciprocal.

862
00:35:38.560 --> 00:35:38.561


863
00:35:38.561 --> 00:35:40.080
For too long,

864
00:35:40.080 --> 00:35:40.081


865
00:35:40.081 --> 00:35:45.720
the American people were told that mammoth multinational trade deals,

866
00:35:45.720 --> 00:35:45.721


867
00:35:45.721 --> 00:35:49.040
unaccountable international tribunals,

868
00:35:49.040 --> 00:35:49.041


869
00:35:49.041 --> 00:35:55.880
and powerful global bureaucracies were the best way to promote their success.

870
00:35:55.880 --> 00:35:55.920


871
00:35:55.920 --> 00:35:59.000
But as those promises flowed,

872
00:35:59.000 --> 00:35:59.001


873
00:35:59.001 --> 00:36:05.160
millions of jobs vanished and thousands of factories disappeared.

874
00:36:05.160 --> 00:36:05.161


875
00:36:05.161 --> 00:36:12.120
Others gamed the system and broke the rules.

876
00:36:12.120 --> 00:36:12.121


877
00:36:12.121 --> 00:36:14.760
And our great middle class,

878
00:36:14.760 --> 00:36:14.761


879
00:36:14.761 --> 00:36:18.920
once the bedrock of American prosperity,

880
00:36:18.920 --> 00:36:18.921


881
00:36:18.921 --> 00:36:22.200
was forgotten and left behind,

882
00:36:22.200 --> 00:36:22.201


883
00:36:22.201 --> 00:36:28.960
but they are forgotten no more and they will never be forgotten again.

884
00:36:28.960 --> 00:36:28.961


885
00:36:28.961 --> 00:36:37.600
While America will pursue cooperation and commerce with other nations,

886
00:36:37.600 --> 00:36:37.601


887
00:36:37.601 --> 00:36:45.600
we are renewing our commitment to the first duty of every government: the duty of our citizens.

888
00:36:45.600 --> 00:36:45.601


889
00:36:45.601 --> 00:36:54.240
This bond is the source of America's strength and that of every responsible nation represented here today.

890
00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:54.241


891
00:36:54.241 --> 00:37:01.280
If this organization is to have any hope of successfully confronting the challenges before us,

892
00:37:01.280 --> 00:37:01.281


893
00:37:01.281 --> 00:37:03.040
it will depend,

894
00:37:03.040 --> 00:37:03.041


895
00:37:03.041 --> 00:37:07.360
as President Truman said some 70 years ago,

896
00:37:07.360 --> 00:37:07.361


897
00:37:07.361 --> 00:37:12.400
on the "independent strength of its members."

898
00:37:12.400 --> 00:37:12.401


899
00:37:12.401 --> 00:37:18.360
If we are to embrace the opportunities of the future and overcome the present dangers together,

900
00:37:18.360 --> 00:37:18.760


901
00:37:18.760 --> 00:37:23.200
there can be no substitute for strong,

902
00:37:23.200 --> 00:37:23.240


903
00:37:23.240 --> 00:37:24.280
sovereign,

904
00:37:24.280 --> 00:37:24.400


905
00:37:24.400 --> 00:37:26.800
and independent nations --

906
00:37:26.800 --> 00:37:26.801


907
00:37:26.801 --> 00:37:33.160
nations that are rooted in their histories and invested in their destinies;

908
00:37:33.160 --> 00:37:33.161


909
00:37:33.161 --> 00:37:36.040
nations that seek allies to befriend,

910
00:37:36.040 --> 00:37:36.041


911
00:37:36.041 --> 00:37:38.560
not enemies to conquer;

912
00:37:38.560 --> 00:37:38.561


913
00:37:38.561 --> 00:37:40.720
and most important of all,

914
00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:40.721


915
00:37:40.721 --> 00:37:43.600
nations that are home to patriots,

916
00:37:43.600 --> 00:37:43.601


917
00:37:43.601 --> 00:37:49.480
to men and women who are willing to sacrifice for their countries,

918
00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:49.520


919
00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:51.120
their fellow citizens,

920
00:37:51.120 --> 00:37:51.121


921
00:37:51.121 --> 00:37:55.720
and for all that is best in the human spirit.

922
00:37:55.720 --> 00:37:55.721


923
00:37:55.721 --> 00:38:00.480
In remembering the great victory that led to this body's founding,

924
00:38:00.480 --> 00:38:00.481


925
00:38:00.481 --> 00:38:10.640
we must never forget that those heroes who fought against evil also fought for the nations that they loved.

926
00:38:10.640 --> 00:38:10.641


927
00:38:10.641 --> 00:38:15.640
Patriotism led the Poles to die to save Poland,

928
00:38:15.640 --> 00:38:15.680


929
00:38:15.680 --> 00:38:19.320
the French to fight for a free France,

930
00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:19.321


931
00:38:19.321 --> 00:38:23.680
and the Brits to stand strong for Britain.

932
00:38:23.680 --> 00:38:23.681


933
00:38:23.681 --> 00:38:24.840
Today,

934
00:38:24.840 --> 00:38:24.841


935
00:38:24.841 --> 00:38:25.840
if we do not invest ourselves,

936
00:38:25.840 --> 00:38:25.841


937
00:38:25.841 --> 00:38:26.920
our hearts,

938
00:38:26.920 --> 00:38:27.360


939
00:38:27.360 --> 00:38:29.000
and our minds in our nations,

940
00:38:29.000 --> 00:38:29.001


941
00:38:29.001 --> 00:38:31.520
if we will not build strong families,

942
00:38:31.520 --> 00:38:31.521


943
00:38:31.521 --> 00:38:33.400
safe communities,

944
00:38:33.400 --> 00:38:33.401


945
00:38:33.401 --> 00:38:36.000
and healthy societies for ourselves,

946
00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:36.001


947
00:38:36.001 --> 00:38:40.600
no one can do it for us.

948
00:38:40.600 --> 00:38:40.601


949
00:38:40.601 --> 00:38:41.960
We cannot wait for someone else,

950
00:38:41.960 --> 00:38:41.961


951
00:38:41.961 --> 00:38:46.440
for faraway countries or far-off bureaucrats --

952
00:38:46.440 --> 00:38:46.441


953
00:38:46.441 --> 00:38:48.400
we can't do it.

954
00:38:48.400 --> 00:38:48.401


955
00:38:48.401 --> 00:38:51.400
We must solve our problems,

956
00:38:51.400 --> 00:38:51.401


957
00:38:51.401 --> 00:38:53.720
to build our prosperity,

958
00:38:53.720 --> 00:38:53.721


959
00:38:53.721 --> 00:38:55.800
to secure our futures,

960
00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:55.801


961
00:38:55.801 --> 00:38:59.000
or we will be vulnerable to decay,

962
00:38:59.000 --> 00:38:59.001


963
00:38:59.001 --> 00:39:00.000
domination,

964
00:39:00.000 --> 00:39:00.040


965
00:39:00.040 --> 00:39:01.400
and defeat.

966
00:39:01.400 --> 00:39:01.401


967
00:39:01.401 --> 00:39:04.480
The true question for the United Nations today,

968
00:39:04.480 --> 00:39:04.481


969
00:39:04.481 --> 00:39:10.600
for people all over the world who hope for better lives for themselves and their children,

970
00:39:10.600 --> 00:39:10.601


971
00:39:10.601 --> 00:39:12.400
is a basic one:

972
00:39:12.400 --> 00:39:12.401


973
00:39:12.401 --> 00:39:22.320
Are we still patriots? Do we love our nations enough to protect their sovereignty and to take ownership of their futures?

974
00:39:22.320 --> 00:39:22.321


975
00:39:22.321 --> 00:39:28.320
Do we revere them enough to defend their interests,

976
00:39:28.320 --> 00:39:28.321


977
00:39:28.321 --> 00:39:30.680
preserve their cultures,

978
00:39:30.680 --> 00:39:30.720


979
00:39:30.720 --> 00:39:35.240
and ensure a peaceful world for their citizens?

980
00:39:35.240 --> 00:39:35.241


981
00:39:35.241 --> 00:39:38.280
One of the greatest American patriots,

982
00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:38.400


983
00:39:38.920 --> 00:39:39.040
John Adams,

984
00:39:39.040 --> 00:39:39.041


985
00:39:39.041 --> 00:39:42.080
wrote that the American Revolution was

986
00:39:42.080 --> 00:39:42.800


987
00:39:42.800 --> 00:39:52.360
"effected before the war commenced. The Revolution was in the minds and hearts of the people."

988
00:39:52.360 --> 00:39:52.361


989
00:39:52.361 --> 00:39:54.200
That was the moment when America awoke,

990
00:39:54.200 --> 00:39:54.201


991
00:39:54.201 --> 00:39:59.400
when we looked around and understood that we were a nation.

992
00:39:59.400 --> 00:39:59.401


993
00:39:59.401 --> 00:40:01.400
We realized who we were,

994
00:40:01.400 --> 00:40:01.401


995
00:40:01.401 --> 00:40:03.160
what we valued,

996
00:40:03.160 --> 00:40:03.161


997
00:40:03.161 --> 00:40:07.360
and what we would give our lives to defend.

998
00:40:07.360 --> 00:40:07.361


999
00:40:07.361 --> 00:40:09.920
From its very first moments,

1000
00:40:09.920 --> 00:40:09.921


1001
00:40:09.921 --> 00:40:18.840
the American story is the story of what is possible when people take ownership of their future.

1002
00:40:18.840 --> 00:40:18.880


1003
00:40:18.880 --> 00:40:25.720
The United States of America has been among the greatest forces for good in the history of the world,

1004
00:40:25.720 --> 00:40:25.721


1005
00:40:25.721 --> 00:40:28.720
and the greatest defenders of sovereignty,

1006
00:40:28.720 --> 00:40:28.721


1007
00:40:28.721 --> 00:40:29.840
security,

1008
00:40:29.840 --> 00:40:29.841


1009
00:40:29.841 --> 00:40:32.160
and prosperity for all.

1010
00:40:32.960 --> 00:40:33.041


1011
00:40:33.041 --> 00:40:39.200
Now we are calling for a great reawakening of nations,

1012
00:40:39.200 --> 00:40:39.201


1013
00:40:39.201 --> 00:40:42.560
for the revival of their spirits,

1014
00:40:42.560 --> 00:40:42.600


1015
00:40:42.600 --> 00:40:43.960
their pride,

1016
00:40:43.960 --> 00:40:43.961


1017
00:40:43.961 --> 00:40:45.480
their people,

1018
00:40:45.480 --> 00:40:45.481


1019
00:40:45.481 --> 00:40:49.200
and their patriotism.

1020
00:40:49.200 --> 00:40:49.201


1021
00:40:49.201 --> 00:40:51.800
History is asking us whether we are up to the task.

1022
00:40:51.800 --> 00:40:51.840


1023
00:40:51.840 --> 00:40:55.760
Our answer will be a renewal of will,

1024
00:40:55.760 --> 00:40:55.761


1025
00:40:55.761 --> 00:40:59.200
a rediscovery of resolve,

1026
00:40:59.200 --> 00:40:59.201


1027
00:40:59.201 --> 00:41:02.360
and a rebirth of devotion.

1028
00:41:02.360 --> 00:41:02.361


1029
00:41:02.361 --> 00:41:11.440
We need to defeat the enemies of humanity and unlock the potential of life itself.

1030
00:41:11.440 --> 00:41:11.441


1031
00:41:11.441 --> 00:41:15.560
Our hope is a word and -- world of proud,

1032
00:41:15.560 --> 00:41:15.561


1033
00:41:15.561 --> 00:41:20.960
independent nations that embrace their duties,

1034
00:41:20.960 --> 00:41:20.961


1035
00:41:20.961 --> 00:41:22.760
seek friendship,

1036
00:41:22.760 --> 00:41:22.800


1037
00:41:22.800 --> 00:41:24.200
respect others,

1038
00:41:24.200 --> 00:41:24.201


1039
00:41:24.201 --> 00:41:28.800
and make common cause in the greatest shared interest of all:

1040
00:41:28.800 --> 00:41:28.801


1041
00:41:28.801 --> 00:41:35.320
a future of dignity and peace for the people of this wonderful Earth.

1042
00:41:35.320 --> 00:41:35.360


1043
00:41:35.360 --> 00:41:39.800
This is the true vision of the United Nations,

1044
00:41:39.800 --> 00:41:39.801


1045
00:41:39.801 --> 00:41:42.600
the ancient wish of every people,

1046
00:41:42.600 --> 00:41:42.601


1047
00:41:42.601 --> 00:41:49.520
and the deepest yearning that lives inside every sacred soul.

1048
00:41:49.520 --> 00:41:49.521


1049
00:41:49.521 --> 00:41:52.200
So let this be our mission,

1050
00:41:52.200 --> 00:41:52.201


1051
00:41:52.201 --> 00:41:55.560
and let this be our message to the world:

1052
00:41:55.560 --> 00:41:55.561


1053
00:41:55.561 --> 00:41:57.920
We will fight together,

1054
00:41:57.920 --> 00:41:57.921


1055
00:41:57.921 --> 00:42:00.120
sacrifice together,

1056
00:42:00.120 --> 00:42:00.160


1057
00:42:00.160 --> 00:42:03.320
and stand together for peace,

1058
00:42:03.320 --> 00:42:03.321


1059
00:42:03.321 --> 00:42:04.520
for freedom,

1060
00:42:05.280 --> 00:42:05.361


1061
00:42:05.361 --> 00:42:06.840
for justice,

1062
00:42:06.840 --> 00:42:06.841


1063
00:42:06.841 --> 00:42:08.160
for family,

1064
00:42:08.160 --> 00:42:08.161


1065
00:42:08.161 --> 00:42:08.560
for humanity,

1066
00:42:08.560 --> 00:42:08.561


1067
00:42:08.561 --> 00:42:14.600
and for the almighty God who made us all.

1068
00:42:14.600 --> 00:42:14.601


1069
00:42:14.601 --> 00:42:15.920
Thank you.

1070
00:42:15.920 --> 00:42:15.921


1071
00:42:15.921 --> 00:42:17.680
God bless you.

1072
00:42:17.680 --> 00:42:17.681


1073
00:42:17.681 --> 00:42:21.120
God bless the nations of the world.

1074
00:42:21.120 --> 00:42:21.121


1075
00:42:21.121 --> 00:42:25.760
And God bless the United States of America.

1076
00:42:25.760 --> 00:42:25.761


1077
00:42:25.761 --> 00:42:41.320
Thank you very much.

1078
00:42:41.320 --> 00:42:41.321


1079
00:42:41.321 --> 00:42:42.680
On behalf of the General Assembly,

1080
00:42:42.680 --> 00:42:42.681


1081
00:42:42.681 --> 00:42:48.120
I wish to thank the President of the United States of America for the statement just made.

1082
00:42:48.120 --> 00:42:48.121


1083
00:42:48.121 --> 00:43:02.440
May I request representatives to remain seated while we greet the president after which the meeting will stand suspended for five minutes before resuming to hear the next speaker.

